===Etymology===
From {{etyl|ML.|en}} {{term|Baioarii||Bavarians|lang=la}}, from {{etyl|LL.|en}} {{term|Bojuvarii|lang=la}}, literally, "[[Boii]] settlers", compound of {{etyl|cel-gau|en}} {{term|Boii||the Boii tribe|lang=cel-gau}} and {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*warjaz||settler}} (compare {{etyl|non|-}} {{term|verjar||defender, settler|lang=non}}), from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}}
(compare {{etyl|cy|-}} {{term|gwerin||crowd|lang=cy}}, {{etyl|sa|-}} {{term|||group, troop, crowd|tr=vṛndám|lang=sa}}). This name was adopted by the [[Marcomanni]] after defeating the Boii and settling [[Bohemia]] and parts of Bavaria.

===Pronunciation===
